1
00:00:49,119 --> 00:00:50,719
Thank you for coming today.

2
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:53,920
To be honest,

3
00:00:54,439 --> 00:00:55,880
I haven't seen so many people for a long time.

4
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:57,320
My editor said

5
00:00:57,439 --> 00:00:59,679
he wanted to hold a new book launch.

6
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:00,840
I said stop it.

7
00:01:01,399 --> 00:01:03,679
For someone who just survived on a deserted island,

8
00:01:03,799 --> 00:01:04,760
I can't see too many people.

9
00:01:05,359 --> 00:01:05,719
Dizzy.

10
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:07,680
Besides,

11
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,239
it's so boring to hold a press conference.

12
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:10,760
A few people sit there,

13
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:13,439
and each thinks he is a high-knowledge cultural elite.

14
00:01:14,159 --> 00:01:15,760
They're all talking in riddles,

15
00:01:15,959 --> 00:01:16,680
not making sense.

16
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:17,319
So boring.

17
00:01:18,359 --> 00:01:19,120
You're reading it so intently.

18
00:01:19,799 --> 00:01:20,599
What did you find?

19
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,200
It feels strange.

20
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:25,560
I can't put my finger on it.

21
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:27,519
This new book

22
00:01:28,439 --> 00:01:30,200
doesn't feel like it was written

23
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,920
by the same person as Galaxy Chronicles.

24
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,719
Because I travel a lot.

25
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:34,719
Well,

26
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:36,439
through my travels over the years,

27
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:39,319
I do have some new ideas and insights.

28
00:01:39,879 --> 00:01:42,239
It's also influencing my personality,

29
00:01:42,359 --> 00:01:43,879
even my life.

30
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:46,799
Wait for me here.

31
00:01:46,799 --> 00:01:47,599
Thank you.

32
00:01:47,959 --> 00:01:49,640
Enjoy yourselves.

33
00:01:51,319 --> 00:01:52,120
Miss Yan.

34
00:01:54,079 --> 00:01:54,840
Miss Yan.

35
00:01:55,239 --> 00:01:56,680
May I ask you a question?

36
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,840
How long have you known Xu Chi?

37
00:01:59,439 --> 00:02:01,400
You seem to have a good understanding of each other.

38
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:02,879
Like you've known each other for a long time.

39
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:07,799
Mr. Wei'an.

40
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:09,599
Here,

41
00:02:09,719 --> 00:02:11,360
I formally introduce myself to you.

42
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:13,400
I'm Yan Ying from Qingyun Country.

43
00:02:14,199 --> 00:02:14,960
Galactic Chronicle

44
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:16,199
is just a novel

45
00:02:16,479 --> 00:02:17,360
in this world,

46
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,039
but the story in it

47
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:21,240
really happened in our world.

48
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:22,919
So,

49
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,560
I hope you can rewrite Galactic Chronicle

50
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,639
and finish the story.

51
00:02:26,919 --> 00:02:28,479
Give the soldiers and people of Qingyun Country

52
00:02:28,919 --> 00:02:30,199
a perfect ending.

53
00:02:35,479 --> 00:02:36,280
Miss Yan,

54
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:39,240
many readers want me to rewrite Galaxy Chronicle,

55
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,120
but I've never heard

56
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,360
such an idea.

57
00:02:43,159 --> 00:02:44,159
No, I really...

58
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,599
Since you like this novel so much,

59
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:46,719
as the author,

60
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,000
I'm very pleased.

61
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:49,719
But,

62
00:02:50,199 --> 00:02:52,120
every book has its own destiny.

63
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:52,960
I'll write

64
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:53,919
until the end.

65
00:02:54,719 --> 00:02:56,080
We have to return to reality.

66
00:02:56,479 --> 00:02:57,159
Live a good life.

67
00:02:58,879 --> 00:03:00,919
So the world in the book is fake.

68
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,560
What about those who were created?

69
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,919
It's fate to accompany you for a while.

70
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:09,719
When the fate ends, continue the next journey

71
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:10,800
and start a new life.

72
00:03:12,159 --> 00:03:13,159
Don't get too carried away.

73
00:03:13,479 --> 00:03:15,199
How about reading my other books?

74
00:03:16,159 --> 00:03:16,960
But I...

75
00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:19,159
I told you to wait for me.

76
00:03:21,039 --> 00:03:23,159
I heard what the great writer Xu said just now.

77
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,080
But I have a different opinion.

78
00:03:25,599 --> 00:03:27,360
The author is not the creator.

79
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:31,120
whether real or fictional,

80
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,680
should be respected.

81
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:37,120
Not everyone can be as free as you.

82
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:39,599
What you think is ridiculous

83
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,439
may be

84
00:03:40,439 --> 00:03:42,919
something others fight for.

85
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:46,680
Well said.

86
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,879
I'll change my mind.

87
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:53,199
You want me to rewrite the ending of Galaxy Chronicle?

88
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:54,800
Sure.

89
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,199
But I have a condition.

90
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,280
I wonder

91
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,240
if you can agree.

92
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:00,439
Yes, I can.

93
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,000
What are you doing?

94
00:04:04,479 --> 00:04:05,560
Miss Yan,

95
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:07,039
is she your girlfriend?

96
00:04:07,159 --> 00:04:07,960
Xu Mengxi?

97
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:09,879
Yes or no?

98
00:04:12,039 --> 00:04:13,599
It seems that I still have a chance.

99
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,720
I need to perform well.

100
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,000
What do you mean?

101
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,639
I'll see Miss Yan later.

102
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,560
Okay.

103
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:24,879
This is the bedroom.

104
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:27,360
This is the kitchen.

105
00:04:28,319 --> 00:04:29,079
This is the living room.

106
00:04:30,199 --> 00:04:30,879
Can I leave now?

107
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:32,959
Oh.

108
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:34,399
It's really nice.

109
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,279
This is the first time I've been here since you moved.

110
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,000
Thanks to Ms. Yan.

111
00:04:39,399 --> 00:04:40,199
No, no.

112
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,079
Tell me,

113
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:44,399
how did it turn into this rascal coming to my house?

114
00:04:45,759 --> 00:04:48,439
This is the condition Mr. Wei'an agreed to rewrite the ending.

115
00:04:48,959 --> 00:04:50,279
I've already promised her,

116
00:04:50,439 --> 00:04:51,680
I can't go back on my word.

117
00:04:52,399 --> 00:04:53,720
Ms Yan,

118
00:04:54,279 --> 00:04:55,680
I need to do some research

119
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:57,160
to rewrite the novel.

120
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,439
Can I stay here for a while

121
00:05:00,879 --> 00:05:01,920
to discuss and revise it?

122
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:02,639
Sure.

123
00:05:02,879 --> 00:05:04,279
This is my home.

124
00:05:06,759 --> 00:05:07,639
He's living off my food.

125
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:08,720
He's good at everything.

126
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:09,759
Yeah.

127
00:05:10,079 --> 00:05:11,800
Mr. Wei'an, you are handsome

128
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:12,879
and talented.

129
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,360
I just like him.

130
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,319
Mr. Wei'an.

131
00:05:17,319 --> 00:05:17,720
Yes?

132
00:05:18,399 --> 00:05:19,360
There are two guest rooms over there.

133
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,519
One for me

134
00:05:20,639 --> 00:05:21,360
and one for you.

135
00:05:23,759 --> 00:05:24,800
So you two

136
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,120
live together?

137
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,560
Yes.

138
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:34,279
Look.

139
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,279
This is the Jumeirah Island in Dubai.

140
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:39,000
The hotel I stayed in

141
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:41,160
is really in the sky and sea.

142
00:05:41,319 --> 00:05:43,120
There is a huge aquarium under it.

143
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,639
I couldn't help but skydiving.

144
00:05:46,319 --> 00:05:48,680
The scenery on Jumeirah Island is really great.

145
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,120
And this is the Sky Restaurant.

146
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,879
You have to sign a life and death contract to go there.

147
00:05:51,879 --> 00:05:52,720
Because you eat while hanging in the air.

148
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:55,120
Mr. Wei'an, you have been to so many places.

149
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,199
You measure the world with your feet?

150
00:05:58,319 --> 00:05:58,839
Look at this.

151
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,199
It's the desert in the Middle East.

152
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,480
It took me seven days to walk

153
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,079
to the Hegra Tomb.

154
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,160
I just wanted to see

155
00:06:06,639 --> 00:06:09,199
the more than 100 stone tombs left in the first century.

156
00:06:09,639 --> 00:06:10,720
Look at this.

157
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:12,839
The desert camp in the United Arab Emirates.

158
00:06:12,839 --> 00:06:14,759
You spent all your time on traveling.

159
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,160
No wonder you haven't handed in your new book for half a year.

160
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,600
Don't set such high standards.

161
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:22,439
The sales of my last book are enough to offset the sales of the next two books.

162
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,680
You don't want to make progress.

163
00:06:25,199 --> 00:06:26,279
I'll write my next book

164
00:06:26,279 --> 00:06:28,120
about food.

165
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,600
Food cultivation stories?

166
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,079
Miss Yan,

167
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,480
you can't eat spicy food.

168
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:50,879
Why are you eating so many chili peppers?

169
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,279
Because...

170
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:54,439
Because I'm afraid

171
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,839
that one day I won't be able to eat them anymore.

172
00:06:58,839 --> 00:06:59,959
A few years ago,

173
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:02,959
I fought against the bear king of the Xiao family.

174
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,360
It was during the Blood Moon,

175
00:07:05,879 --> 00:07:07,079
which was my doom.

176
00:07:07,879 --> 00:07:10,519
But I don't know when the blood moon will come.

177
00:07:11,079 --> 00:07:12,160
So from then on,

178
00:07:12,759 --> 00:07:14,079
I only have two wishes.

179
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,480
One is to protect my Qingyun State well.

180
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:21,079
The other is to eat all the delicacies in the world.

181
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,240
If you can't eat spicy food,

182
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:25,639
then you've lost half of the delicacies.

183
00:07:26,399 --> 00:07:27,199
Ah.

184
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:29,000
War Bear King.

185
00:07:29,519 --> 00:07:32,600
Chapter 275 of Galaxy Chronicle, Yan Ying fights the Bear King.

186
00:07:33,879 --> 00:07:34,680
Oh.

187
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:37,000
Ah, right.

188
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:39,680
It doesn't matter.

189
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,279
You can practice eating spicy food.

190
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,319
Come on.

191
00:07:43,959 --> 00:07:44,439
OK.

192
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,120
Eat it.

193
00:08:08,079 --> 00:08:08,720
What are you doing?

194
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:11,360
Sleeping. What else can I do?

195
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:13,560
Are you really going to stay here?

196
00:08:13,879 --> 00:08:14,480
Or what?

197
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:16,319
Where should I go at this time of night?

198
00:08:17,199 --> 00:08:18,480
The sofa outside is big enough.

199
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,600
It's not easy for me to come here.

200
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,399
Can you bear to let me sleep on the sofa?

201
00:08:23,839 --> 00:08:24,399
Sleep by yourself.

202
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:28,439
Why are you shy? We used to sleep in the same bed.

203
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,320
I chatted with Yan Ying for a while.

204
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:34,840
What did you talk about?

205
00:08:35,399 --> 00:08:35,919
Nothing.

206
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:37,200
Why are you so nervous?

207
00:08:38,879 --> 00:08:40,480
But your girlfriend

208
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,120
is indeed different from others.

209
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:46,200
She insists that she is the heroine in Galaxy Chronicle.

210
00:08:46,919 --> 00:08:48,879
She wants me to help her rewrite the ending.

211
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:50,720
Since you say you are Wei'an,

212
00:08:51,679 --> 00:08:52,519
you can do as you please.

213
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,679
You know that

214
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,159
I protected you back then.

215
00:08:57,919 --> 00:08:59,360
I've made it clear in my statement.

216
00:08:59,519 --> 00:09:00,600
I am Wei'an.

217
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,000
You are right.

218
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,919
It's my fault.

219
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,000
Yan Ying,

220
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:34,720
what kind of ending do you want?
